<TITLE> US pledges $10 million Food for Peace aid </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 27 (bdnews24.com)  The US Agency for International Development (USAID) has pledged to contribute more than $10 million under the Food for Peace programme for post-Sidr relief and recovery efforts. The aid package includes more than 3,000 tons of Food for Peace assistance as part of CARE and Save the Children grants provided through USAID. The United States, in addition to CARE and Save the Children grants, has provided more than $14.4 million in emergency funds, commodities and transportation to assist relief efforts. "This food aid is not just a life-saving measure but a visible demonstration of the goodwill of the American people to Bangladeshis in their time of need," said Michael Hess, USAID assistant administrator for democracy, conflict and humanitarian assistance, in a US embassy press statement Tuesday. bdnew
